defs.docs:
A simple map based on a vector for small integer keys. Space requirements
 are O(highest integer key).

defs.name: VecMap
defs.docs: A map optimized for small integer keys.

defs.name: Vacant
defs.docs: A vacant Entry

defs.name: Occupied
defs.docs: An occupied Entry

defs.name: Entry
defs.docs: A view into a single entry in a map, which may either be vacant or occupied.

defs.name: VacantEntry
defs.docs: A vacant Entry.

defs.name: OccupiedEntry
defs.docs: An occupied Entry.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Creates an empty `VecMap`.

defs.name: with_capacity
defs.docs:
Creates an empty `VecMap` with space for at least `capacity`
 elements before resizing.

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs:
Returns the number of elements the `VecMap` can hold without
 reallocating.

defs.name: reserve_len
defs.docs:
Reserves capacity for the given `VecMap` to contain `len` distinct keys.
 In the case of `VecMap` this means reallocations will not occur as long
 as all inserted keys are less than `len`.

defs.name: reserve_len_exact
defs.docs:
Reserves the minimum capacity for the given `VecMap` to contain `len` distinct keys.
 In the case of `VecMap` this means reallocations will not occur as long as all inserted
 keys are less than `len`.

defs.name: shrink_to_fit
defs.docs: Trims the `VecMap` of any excess capacity.

defs.name: keys
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator visiting all keys in ascending order of the keys.
 The iterator's element type is `usize`.

defs.name: values
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator visiting all values in ascending order of the keys.
 The iterator's element type is `&'r V`.

defs.name: values_mut
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator visiting all values in ascending order of the keys.
 The iterator's element type is `&'r mut V`.

defs.name: iter
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator visiting all key-value pairs in ascending order of the keys.
 The iterator's element type is `(usize, &'r V)`.

defs.name: iter_mut
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator visiting all key-value pairs in ascending order of the keys,
 with mutable references to the values.
 The iterator's element type is `(usize, &'r mut V)`.

defs.name: append
defs.docs: Moves all elements from `other` into the map while overwriting existing keys.

defs.name: split_off
defs.docs: Splits the collection into two at the given key.

defs.name: drain
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator visiting all key-value pairs in ascending order of
 the keys, emptying (but not consuming) the original `VecMap`.
 The iterator's element type is `(usize, &'r V)`. Keeps the allocated memory for reuse.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the number of elements in the map.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns true if the map contains no elements.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Clears the map, removing all key-value pairs.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Returns a reference to the value corresponding to the key.

defs.name: contains_key
defs.docs: Returns true if the map contains a value for the specified key.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.value: fn (&mut self, key: usize) -> Option<&mut V>
defs.docs: Returns a mutable reference to the value corresponding to the key.

defs.name: insert
defs.value: fn (&mut self, key: usize, value: V) -> Option<V>
defs.docs:
Inserts a key-value pair into the map. If the key already had a value
 present in the map, that value is returned. Otherwise, `None` is returned.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs:
Removes a key from the map, returning the value at the key if the key
 was previously in the map.

defs.name: entry
defs.docs: Gets the given key's corresponding entry in the map for in-place manipulation.

defs.name: retain
defs.docs: Retains only the elements specified by the predicate.

defs.name: or_insert
defs.docs:
Ensures a value is in the entry by inserting the default if empty, and
 returns a mutable reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: or_insert_with
defs.docs:
Ensures a value is in the entry by inserting the result of the default
 function if empty, and returns a mutable reference to the value in the
 entry.

defs.name: insert
defs.docs:
Sets the value of the entry with the VacantEntry's key,
 and returns a mutable reference to it.

defs.name: get
defs.docs: Gets a reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: get_mut
defs.docs: Gets a mutable reference to the value in the entry.

defs.name: into_mut
defs.docs: Converts the entry into a mutable reference to its value.

defs.name: insert
defs.docs:
Sets the value of the entry with the OccupiedEntry's key,
 and returns the entry's old value.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Takes the value of the entry out of the map, and returns it.

defs.name: Iter
defs.docs: An iterator over the key-value pairs of a map.

defs.name: IterMut
defs.docs:
An iterator over the key-value pairs of a map, with the
 values being mutable.

defs.name: Keys
defs.docs: An iterator over the keys of a map.

defs.name: Values
defs.docs: An iterator over the values of a map.

defs.name: ValuesMut
defs.docs: An iterator over the values of a map.

defs.name: IntoIter
defs.docs: A consuming iterator over the key-value pairs of a map.

defs.name: Drain
defs.docs: A draining iterator over the key-value pairs of a map.
